Turkish parliament approves law to register gold . Turkey ' s parliament approved a draft law on Wednesday which will allow jewellers to declare their unregistered physical inventories of precious metals . According to the law , jewellers will not face any punishment for their unregistered stocks if they declare them within one month from the publication of the law in the official gazette . They will pay a six - percent tax on gold bullion and seven percent on other precious metals . The law is part of the government ' s revenue - raising package unveiled in September . It hopes to raise 64 trillion lira through the plan . Officials said 700 tonnes of precious metals were expected to be declared under the law . 
